e global crisis of displacement and the impact of violence and armed conflict on young people, Pelley focuses on the reciprocal adaptation that is required for the long-term integration of displaced youth into the receiving society.A concise and illuminating study on refugee resettlement, Finding Safe Harbour concludes with an in-depth discussion of how cities can optimize resilience resources through meaningful engagement with refugee youth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRefugee childrenxServices forzNova ScotiazHalifax. 0aTeenage refugeesxServices forzNova ScotiazHalifax. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aAntigonish.  aBridgewater.  aCYRRC.  aHalifax.  aISANS.  aKentville.  aNSOI.  aSydney.  aTeacher.  aTruro.  aUnion.  aYMCA.  aYarmouth.  aanti-racism.  abureaucrats.  aengagement.  aexperience.  aimmigration.  aintegration.  alocal.  amunicipal.  anewcomer.  apartnership.  apolicy.  aprograms.  arefugee.  aresettlement.  aservices.  aworkers.  ayouth.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801003640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228010036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228010036/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles